column5: I got gas in Dryden today @ $1.13 per litre.

I have found that this is very helpful for our group in determining or rather, guesstimating what our fuel costs might be when we get there. Go to google and do a search for "Canada Gas Prices" and you will come up with a couple of sites to pick towns or regions close to where you are going to find prices.
Check gasbuddy.com for all Canadian Provinces and US States.
